Post Description:
E-Mail Received:
"{Company name redacted as a courtesy} is adjusting our pricing to more accurately reflect the value our users get from the tool. Effective 01/01/2020, your contract fee will increase by 10% to 15%."

A few thoughts for #meetingprofs and #supplierpartners related to #customerservice, #sales and how to manage #relationships with partners:

1) Don't email the wrong contact for an organization who has managed your #EventTech contract for multiple years;

2) Don't wait until renewal time discuss pricing increases; budgeting decisions have already been made and set into action;

3) Come at me with a number, not some arbitrary range of an increase;

4) Don't assume someone else's value proposition on your product, especially when you contact the wrong person and we only hear from you during the renewal cycle;

5) Finally, first and foremost, thank the customer before you do anything else, especially if you're going to drop a price increase bomb on them.

Let me be clear, this experience is in the minority. We have worked really hard to establish great relationships with many of our #EventTech and other partners. This company, however, just lost our business.
